text: Milwaukee County is a county in the U.S. state of Wisconsin. As of the 2020 census, the population was 939,489. It is the largest county in Wisconsin and the 45th in the United States. Its county seat is Milwaukee, which is also the most populous city in the state. The county was created in 1835. ==References== Category:Wisconsin counties Category:1835 establishments in Michigan Territory
title: Milwaukee County, Wisconsin
